network_overview: The capture contains only IMS-based VoLTE/VoNR SIP signaling between P-CSCF and S-CSCF/AS nodes; every call leg is challenged with SIP 407 (proxy authentication required) and later cancelled or times-out, so no bearer (RTP) is ever established. No GTP, Diameter, or media-plane traffic is present, indicating a pure control-plane recording on the Mw/N6 interface.

observations.finding: 100 % of INVITEs receive 407 Proxy Authentication Required; second INVITE (with credentials) is sent but every call is later CANCELLED or times-out, so 0 % call-completion rate.
No RTP flows detected; media bearer never established, hence voice service is effectively unavailable during the trace window.
SIP transaction RTTs are healthy (< 100 ms) and no retransmissions occur, so transport and IMS routing are not the bottleneck.

root_causes.description: All initial INVITEs are rejected with SIP 407, indicating the P-CSCF is correctly requesting authentication. However, after the second INVITE (with credentials) reaches 180 Ringing, the originating side abandons the call (CANCEL) or lets it time-out, suggesting an upstream service (MMTel AS, ENUM, or called-party reachability) never returns 200 OK.
root_causes.impact: Complete call-setup failure; subscribers cannot originate or receive voice calls.

root_causes.description: No Diameter traffic is captured, so the PCRF is never contacted for bearer-authorization; without an Rx AAR the PGW/UPF will not establish a dedicated QCI=1 bearer, preventing the network from sending a 183 with SDP that would trigger radio access to reserve resources.
root_causes.impact: Bearer reservation failure leads to prolonged alerting state and eventual cancellation.

recommendations.action: Check S-CSCF/MMTel logs for the two call-ids that reached 180 Ringing; verify why neither received a final 200 OK within 25 s (normal post-alerting timeout).
recommendations.rationale: Identifies whether the failure is in the terminating MMTel AS, called-party IMS registration, or PSTN gateway.

recommendations.action: Enable Rx interface capture between P-CSCF and PCRF; confirm an AAR is sent immediately after the second INVITE and that the PCRF returns an AAA with QCI=1 and acceptable bit-rate.
recommendations.rationale: Bearer authorization must succeed before the terminating side can be alerted with guaranteed QoS; absence of Rx explains bearer-less 180 state.

recommendations.action: Validate that the P-CSCF adds the correct P-Access-Network-Info and P-Charging-Vector headers so downstream nodes can resolve the calling party’s MMTel profile and terminating domain.
recommendations.rationale: Missing or malformed headers can cause AS to silently drop the call, leaving it in alerting state.

recommendations.action: Review timer settings: T alerting (typically 30 s) and T guard (15 s) in S-CSCF; reduce if operator policy allows faster timeout to release resources earlier.
recommendations.rationale: Shortens resource reservation window and improves perceived service responsiveness while root cause is fixed.

session_analysis.signaling_health: SIP transactions are syntactically correct and timely; however every call ends in CANCEL or time-out, so control-plane success rate is 0 %.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP-U or RTP detected; dedicated bearer (QCI=1) is never established, hence user-plane is non-existent.
session_analysis.voice_quality: No media stream means MOS, packet-loss, and jitter cannot be assessed; from a subscriber perspective voice service is unavailable.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Signaling reaches 180 Ringing but absence of Rx/Diameter prevents bearer creation; without the bearer the call cannot complete, correlating control-plane progress with user-plane failure.

    UE->>P-CSCF: INVITE (with auth)
    P-CSCF->>S-CSCF: INVITE
    S-CSCF->>MMTelAS: INVITE
    MMTelAS-->>S-CSCF: 180 Ringing
    S-CSCF-->>P-CSCF: 180 Ringing
    P-CSCF-->>UE: 180 Ringing
    Note over UE,MMTelAS: Bearer auth missing, no 200 OK
    UE->>P-CSCF: CANCEL (after 25 s)
    P-CSCF->>UE: 200 CANCEL OK
    P-CSCF->>UE: 487 Request Terminated
    UE->>P-CSCF: ACK
